49/*
50can have any number of princ stanzas.
51format is as follows (only \n indicates newlines)
52princ\t%d\t (%d is KRB5_KDB_V1_BASE_LENGTH, always 38)
53%d\t (strlen of principal e.g. shadow/foo@ANDREW.CMU.EDU)
54%d\t (number of tl_data)
55%d\t (number of key data, e.g. how many keys for this user)
56%d\t (extra data length)
57%s\t (principal name)
58%d\t (attributes)
59%d\t (max lifetime, seconds)
60%d\t (max renewable life, seconds)
61%d\t (expiration, seconds since epoch or 2145830400 for never)
62%d\t (password expiration, seconds, 0 for never)
63%d\t (last successful auth, seconds since epoch)
64%d\t (last failed auth, per above)
65%d\t (failed auth count)
66foreach tl_data 0 to number of tl_data - 1 as above
67 %d\t%d\t (data type, data length)
68 foreach tl_data 0 to length-1
69 %02x (tl data contents[element n])
70 except if tl_data length is 0
71 %d (always -1)
72 \t
73foreach key 0 to number of keys - 1 as above
74 %d\t%d\t (key data version, kvno)
75 foreach version 0 to key data version - 1 (a key or a salt)
76 %d\t%d\t(data type for this key, data length for this key)
77 foreach key data length 0 to length-1
78 %02x (key data contents[element n])
79 except if key_data length is 0
80 %d (always -1)
81 \t
82foreach extra data length 0 to length - 1
83 %02x (extra data part)
84unless no extra data
85 %d (always -1)
86;\n
87
88*/
89
90static char *
91nexttoken(char **p)
92{
93 char *q;
94 do {
95 q = strsep(p, " \t");
96 } while(q && *q == '\0');
97 return q;
98}
99
100#include <kadm5/admin.h>
101
102/* XXX This is broken: what if the princ name has a \n?! */
103static int
104my_fgetln(FILE *f, char **buf, size_t *sz, size_t *len)
105{
106 char *p, *n;
107
108 if (!*buf) {
109 *buf = malloc(*sz ? *sz : 2048);
110 if (!*buf)
111 return ENOMEM;
112 if (!*sz)
113 *sz = 2048;
114 }
115 *len = 0;
116 while ((p = fgets(&(*buf)[*len], *sz - *len, f))) {
117 *len = strlen(*buf);
118 if (feof(f))
119 return 0;
120 if (strchr(*buf, '\n'))
121 return 0;
122 n = realloc(*buf, *sz + (*sz >> 1));
123 if (!n) {
124 free(*buf);
125 *buf = NULL;
126 *sz = 0;
127 *len = 0;
128 return ENOMEM;
129 }
130 *buf = n;
131 *sz += *sz >> 1;
132 }
133 return 0; /* *len == 0 || no EOL -> EOF */
134}
135
136int
137mit_prop_dump(void *arg, const char *file)
138{
139 krb5_error_code ret;
140 size_t line_bufsz = 0;
141 size_t line_len = 0;
142 char *line = NULL;
143 int lineno = 0;
144 FILE *f;
145 struct hdb_entry_ex ent;
146 struct prop_data *pd = arg;
147 krb5_storage *sp = NULL;
148 krb5_data kdb_ent;
149
150 memset(&ent, 0, sizeof (ent));
151 f = fopen(file, "r");
152 if (f == NULL)
153 return errno;
154
155 ret = ENOMEM;
156 sp = krb5_storage_emem();
157 if (!sp)
158 goto out;
159 while ((ret = my_fgetln(f, &line, &line_bufsz, &line_len)) == 0 &&
160 !feof(f)) {
161 char *p = line;
162 char *q;
163 lineno++;
164
165 if(strncmp(line, "kdb5_util", strlen("kdb5_util")) == 0) {
166 int major;
167 q = nexttoken(&p);
168 if (strcmp(q, "kdb5_util"))
169 errx(1, "line %d: unknown version", lineno);
170 q = nexttoken(&p); /* load_dump */
171 if (strcmp(q, "load_dump"))
172 errx(1, "line %d: unknown version", lineno);
173 q = nexttoken(&p); /* load_dump */
174 if (strcmp(q, "version"))
175 errx(1, "line %d: unknown version", lineno);
176 q = nexttoken(&p); /* x.0 */
177 if (sscanf(q, "%d", &major) != 1)
178 errx(1, "line %d: unknown version", lineno);
179 if (major != 4 && major != 5 && major != 6)
180 errx(1, "unknown dump file format, got %d, expected 4-6",
181 major);
182 continue;
183 } else if(strncmp(p, "policy", strlen("policy")) == 0) {
184 warnx("line: %d: ignoring policy (not supported)", lineno);
185 continue;
186 } else if(strncmp(p, "princ", strlen("princ")) != 0) {
187 warnx("line %d: not a principal", lineno);
188 continue;
189 }
190 krb5_storage_truncate(sp, 0);
191 ret = _hdb_mit_dump2mitdb_entry(pd->context, line, sp);
192 if (ret) {
193 if (ret > 0)
194 warn("line: %d: failed to parse; ignoring", lineno);
195 else
196 warnx("line: %d: failed to parse; ignoring", lineno);
197 continue;
198 }
199 ret = krb5_storage_to_data(sp, &kdb_ent);
200 if (ret) break;
201 ret = _hdb_mdb_value2entry(pd->context, &kdb_ent, 0, &ent.entry);
202 krb5_data_free(&kdb_ent);
203 if (ret) {
204 warnx("line: %d: failed to store; ignoring", lineno);
205 continue;
206 }
207 ret = v5_prop(pd->context, NULL, &ent, arg);
208 hdb_free_entry(pd->context, &ent);
209 if (ret) break;
210 }
211
212out:
213 fclose(f);
214 free(line);
215 if (sp)
216 krb5_storage_free(sp);
217 if (ret && ret == ENOMEM)
218 errx(1, "out of memory");
219 if (ret)
220 errx(1, "line %d: problem parsing dump line", lineno);
221 return ret;
222}
